snippet.textDisplay:
This song is deeper than you think it is. Many foreigners when visit pakistan Northern Areas which are Pakhtoon homelands, they fell in love with the place and hospitality of the local people. 

In this song a Girl ( a foreigner) fell in love with this Magical People and its cultural that represnt the beauty of land. And despite there differences they come together. Harlakay!  

I'm no Pakhtoon. I'm Punjabi and I understand the messege.

The male vocals (Zahoor) are fire. So, so good. I could listen to them over and over again. 

I think the song misses something by transitioning to English. I get the concept but, the texture and depth of parts in Pashto is remarkable, that English just can't match.
